content:
Every Einstein Bot requires a primary language to understand end users. Defining a bot's primary language helps with natural language processing (NLP) and named entity recognition (NER).

To set a primary language for the bot:

* Go to Setup, enter "Einstein Bots" in Quick Find
* Click New, select the type of bot, click Next
* Select the bot's default language, click Next, complete setup steps

Alternatively, edit the Bot Overview section of the Overview menu.

Note: If secondary languages are added, you can't update the primary language.
title: Setting a Primary Language for Einstein Bots
